<div class="modal fade" id="productsHelp" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="productsHelpLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="productsHelpLabel">Products Help</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Purpose</h6>
                    <p>This screen manages SKU master data and unit-of-measure configurations for inventory operations.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Index (List)</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Filter by SKU code, name, category, brand, or EAN.</li>
                        <li>Use Status and Include Inactive to control visibility.</li>
                        <li>Sort by clicking column headers.</li>
                        <li>Use pagination and page size to navigate large catalogs.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Create</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Click <strong>New Product</strong> to create a SKU.</li>
                        <li>Required fields: Code, Name, Base UoM, Tracking Mode.</li>
                        <li>Tracking Mode defines whether lots and expiry are enforced.</li>
                        <li>Minimum Shelf Life defines the minimum days until expiration required for receipts.</li>
                        <li>Optional fields: Description, EAN, ERP code, category, brand, dimensions, weight.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Details</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Review SKU master data and dimension/weight details.</li>
                        <li>Tracking Mode is displayed in the core details section.</li>
                        <li>Manage UoM conversions (add conversion factors for packaging).</li>
                        <li>Navigate to Lots for the selected product if needed.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Edit</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Update SKU information and dimensions.</li>
                        <li>Base UoM changes should be consistent with conversions.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h6>Deactivate</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Deactivate a SKU from the Delete action.</li>
                        <li>Inactive products can be included via filters.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h6>Common Issues</h6>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><strong>Code/EAN/ERP already used:</strong> each must be unique per customer.</li>
                        <li><strong>Tracking mismatch:</strong> lots require Tracking Mode Lot or Lot and expiry.</li>
                        <li><strong>Quarantine on receipt:</strong> lots with less remaining shelf life than the product rule will be quarantined.</li>
                        <li><strong>Invalid dimensions:</strong> values must be positive when provided.</li>
                        <li><strong>Missing Base UoM:</strong> create the unit first in UoM.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-light border" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
